Class LinkedAbstractList<E>

  • java.lang.Object

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type in the LinkedAbstractList
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>

    public class LinkedAbstractList<E>
extends java.util.AbstractList<E>
    This is a custom LinkedAbstractList that does not allow for null elements or duplicate elements by the equals() method. This list also has a capacity. This class will be implemented in the CourseRoll class
    Author:
    jhnguye4

      • LinkedAbstractList

        public LinkedAbstractList(int capacity)
        Constructor of the LinkedAbstractList that has one parameter. The parameter will indicate the capacity of the linked list and will be used to set limits to how many students can enroll in a class. The size will be set to 0 and the capacity will be set in the setter method to error check and throw exceptions.
        Parameters:
        capacity - is the size of the list
